info.description: Made by joining together 4 thin plates, those in the part being smaller then those at the back, giving the appearance of a stud. The smaller plate ornamented with wheel-like figure of dots; attached by a recurved edge to an unornamented plate, which has an opening in the centre, this is joined to the edges of an opening in the 3rd plate, which is joined by an overlapping rim to the outermost plate. The latter is externally ornamented with 5 raised circles surrounded by dots placed on a five-limbed figure contained in a dotted circle. in the space between the central plates was found a small solid gold ball weighing .715 gms. [;] Wilde:- "when found the plates were crushed flat & there were indentations of 3 such balls in both the external plates."

info.description: The upper plate of one of the terminal bosses is missing. Decorated with 7 unornamented ribs, between which are bars decorated with rope work. The complete terminal boss has its upper surface decorated with a central spike, & 14 small knobs surrounded by concentric circles. The lower plate of the terminal discs are decorated with 5 rows of circular knobs, each row being divided by rope work. The end of the gorget was passed into a slit at the back of the lower disc, where it was attached by a corrugated line burnished into a corresponding one in the collar. The wire stitchings now to be seen, do not appear to be ancient.
